e a public API for a bean, but it’s only active within the Mixin class. I want to make sure there’s no dollar sign ($) in the file name, which is good to keep in mind. The MixinTest seems fine, so I’ll have to write it out clearly to cover everything. Let’s make sure it’s well-structured!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_J0d2TitYBpPy8rUEEfXXNW7g|fc_0567b4fe487dee770169fb9afbcb3c8194ae92dd6351607f67", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MixinTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.proxy.Mixin;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class MixinTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void discoversInterfacesImplementedByDelegates() {\n        try {\n            Class<?>[] classes = Mixin.getClasses(new Object[] {new GreeterAndCounter()});\n\n            assertThat(classes).containsExactlyInAnyOrder(Greeter.class, Counter.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(error) == null) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Error findUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error\n                    && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return error;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    public interface Greeter {\n        String greet(String name);\n    }\n\n    public interface Counter {\n        int count();\n    }\n\n    private static final class GreeterAndCounter implements Greeter, Counter {\n        @Override\n        public String greet(String name) {\n            return \"Hello, \" + name;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int count() {\n            return 2;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 429, "output": 1212, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19561, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778096878114, "responseId": "resp_0567b4fe487dee770169fb9aeec4b4819498940240fea5bf3e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_J0d2TitYBpPy8rUEEfXXNW7g|fc_0567b4fe487dee770169fb9afbcb3c8194ae92dd6351607f67", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1656 bytes to tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MixinTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778096893421}]}
