[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering exceptions and interfaces**\n\nI should think about adding helper functions to manage exceptions, which could help reduce duplication in the code. I need to remember that `Mixin.create` returns a Mixin object that implements interfaces, and there's some upstream casting happening. A CGLIB generated subclass of Mixin will also implement those interfaces, so I can use `Greeter greeter = (Greeter) mixin;` for that. I wonder if I should clarify how delegates route ensures that interface methods properly call delegates, especially in explicit interface routing.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0567b4fe487dee770169fb9c8e22288194b243a06c105b41b2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-5yYVCP8J3c22TLJl0tDxX8OGwIpdYpcRBQmp983G42jiqxUCUfMyg6cYzg3oeD-QuVtDNUKC2P6ThTgEEzQtct2UQxBozeinq3Iv83kGAtUsT9rXe6tsrInL3eZJh2N7EyKuHJZ_KFZgIJxxDf9H2x3WqFbVAUnW0zS6fPoqjFRkaPsggY704XPEdKdNoPRNsYMw-FxlYWn59iIXLEN5Pyn96Bs6pOJmhSBtyR_zKNaTMkjbHoyHpe2oIzo4xHJn-i6SkY_G8l7bSIAMBAQsBFxYRw-VH5uMx1_RSbiXOHuo9gFtGOmdUtbzyFKsEHim5FDxu43m6Dm5oIbN6aNF2rRgH777ZnDibeSWMR8OHOCPCo2xVVC3g69n2zAYHQXQLjOKw3F9uvvTa-0VDnj7aK1MpCetjy2vZw87p1-SbsKYNA6YPoU96XxxkWnVBUpauJN1CTzpvF0C-F42gbDrTuA1Uj7rwus35LMZ0kW0_zL_xaocWV7_7O1mgoYT82Dr8uDz8tkDthdl3cvjc9twJqsXKn3xe6eanTTIOqsLskVagkpvzw9LMbFa67dW1RAIcOgt7IOXV6apqu3w2TaUvb9PF1QJkWnW9MB4RqLWP2ZrtiodJ1paE2pLsaLCgQCIO4qFNvSF7Z78ETCiVWHUCjPaHyHmBNPy_f-aHVu4rKzbmImqYABWEuN573IcLqw5Db8f8dIiGagATbSpUF-DguW3P2_KI1iuLdDiB7LSJUEAfqlF1OgIXVilh-kO2VlRw8lY0buTTj5yIKax0bF0hdd56DJ1SUeWt3iWZF8xyEoVLXksdVWGfrtyDnzaE23RtAnuT-9__sn37cVjVizPRb1Ggjlv-ZsyyA0z-0CuoeLEPEcbXj2HjKUu2O8vSkQ3pHhiWrgDhowWqtB9-z65PWoaTaqlpToUxm_KAn4MKZlRTgEIapYsWJ0XCSFstgEA80i32Xrr_HL2yHdekw8afbCjUt3DmnDH_g02GSw7uwxK-9xwbuaXB2L3KBuFz8WOTLqDLK3ZUDqAHYe7V9_v6HfQwijU8PKD8w6Ro0ntfaUQ_Q10q3L3hN0cSuUsnSskEgHwENVrrcQDb8r-2_TgeSNqH0iVySWu7wpZdYOejyenNbS0YWZ6wyfkEY2-FyITw3kI5u_Vxp6YLek-Yt