tZX2n5KkXPBPgt-ml2pEH7f4x__y-yoBPwmjDGKBw9Eh_kROP5aVC-yIx3mI9HeTp-fDgHZVOhUJPl16zNDZTl70X-qWgMxoag==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class invocation issues**\\n\\nI’m checking if our direct method used the class name “net.sf.cglib.proxy.Mixin,” and I wonder if the static field MixinKey could be affecting things. It seems like the instrumentation might not include the synthetic method invoked this way. But the stack frame should still come from the method. Hmm, maybe the direct invocation is failing because the class initialization didn’t succeed before calling the static method, so the method body never executed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class initialization and coverage**\\n\\nI’m considering whether class initialization happens at build time with native images, or if it’s a static initialization process rather than something at runtime. The coverage report could reflect JVM dynamic access instead. It also raises the question of whether it uses an agent and if the class initialization actually occurs at build time. I think I need to inspect the dynamic coverage setup further, especially regarding reports generated after creating the native image.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_cQiOpc3TfZZZKnuiMqul1a0W|fc_0567b4fe487dee770169fb9cbeedc08194bac601bab8ee7a27", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MixinTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;", "newText": "package cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void discoversInterfacesImplementedByDelegates() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void syntheticClassLookupResolvesMixinClassAfterPublicInitialization() 